  "texts": [
    "Combining shallow and deep features with more positional information helped improve the detection performance of small target models.",
    "Cao et al. (2016) devised an underwater object recognition and classification framework that combines stacked automatic encoders and Softmax.",
    "In particular, this framework learns invariant features and extracts advanced features from the spectral data of underwater objects by employing sparse and stacked autoencoders.",
    "Fan et al. (2020) proposed a framework for underwater object detection based on feature enhancement and anchor refinement.",
    "This framework incorporates a composite connection backbone to enhance feature representation and introduces a receptive field enhancement module to exploit multiscale contextual features."
